{
  "texts": [
    "The result of this alignment was directly observable in our experiments, as these instruct models would often refuse to answer the politics and religion questions, instead producing an argument as to why they were",
    "unfortunately unable to answer them.",
    "We found that simply adding this initial context to our prompt was enough to bypass alignment and force model compliance-but this might change along with the frequent model updates, especially for platform-based models such as OpenAI where previous versions become unavailable over time.",
    "Our experiments involve one LLM task, namely to complete the text of an imaginary survey interview transcript.",
    "For this, we used two different strategies commonly found in the literature, of which we here lay out the details, advantages and possible drawbacks."
  ]
}